Wash and dry produce.

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, half the @Garlic Powder{1%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}; bring to a boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced, whites separated from greens). Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb} until you have 1 tsp (2 tsp for 4 servings). Trim and discard root end from @Baby Lettuce{1}(trimmed, leaves separated); separate leaves. Trim and thinly slice @Radishes{3}(sliced into rounds).

Pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Cut lengthwise into 1-inch-thick strips, then halve strips crosswise. In a #medium bowl{}, toss chicken with half the @Korean Spicy Bulgogi Marinade{1}(you'll use the rest of the marinade later) until coated. Set aside to marinate, at least ~{10%minutes}.

== Quick-Picked Cabbage Slaw ==

In a second medium #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}, @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%tsp}, scallion whites, ginger, and @Sugar{1 1/2%tsp} (3 tsp for 4 servings). Cover with #plastic wrap{} and microwave until cabbage is warmed through, ~{45-60%seconds}. Carefully remove plastic wrap and stir. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

== Garlic Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @Mayonnaise{4%tbsp}, remaining @Garlic Powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

== Battering and Frying ==

In a large, microwave-safe bowl, whisk together @Flour{1/2%cup}, @Cornstarch{2%tbsp}, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Working one piece at a time, press marinated chicken into flour mixture and toss until coated in a thick layer. Set aside on a #plate{}.

Discard any remaining flour mixture in bowl; wash and dry bowl.

Heat a 1⁄3-inch layer of @Cooking Oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Once oil is hot enough that a pinch of flour mixture sizzles when added to the pan, add chicken in a single layer (you may need to work in batches for 4 servings). Cook until chicken begins to brown, ~{2-3%minutes} (lower heat if chicken begins to brown too quickly).

Flip and cook until golden brown, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Remove pan from heat; transfer chicken to a #paper-towel-lined plate{} (do not discard oil!). Let chicken rest for ~{2-3%minutes} (you'll finish cooking it in the next step).

Return pan with oil to medium-high heat. Once oil is hot, return fried chicken to pan in a single layer. Cook until deeply browned and cooked through, 1-2 minutes per side. Discard used paper towels; line plate with a fresh layer. Transfer chicken to paper-towel-lined plate.

Place @Butter{2%tbsp} in empty bowl used for flour. Microwave until melted, ~{20-30%seconds}, then whisk in remaining @Korean Spicy Bulgogi Marinade{1}.

Add fried chicken to bowl; toss to coat.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Transfer rice to a #serving bowl{}.

Place lettuce on a #platter{} along with rice, spicy fried chicken, pickled cabbage, and radishes. Sprinkle scallion greens over spicy fried chicken and pickled cabbage.

Serve family style, with garlic mayo on the side for dipping or drizzling.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.